headlines.description: — Coby White scored 27 points in his return to his home state, Andre Drummond added 21 points and 15 rebounds and the Chicago Bulls overcame a 39-point performance from Terry Rozier to beat the Charlotte Hornets 119-112 in overtime on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Coby White scores 27 as Bulls hold on to beat Hornets 119-112 in OT

headlines.description: — Bennedict Mathurin scored 26 points, including the deciding free throws with 0.6 seconds remaining, and the Indiana Pacers rallied after All-Star point guard Tyrese Haliburton suffered a hamstring injury to beat the Boston Celtics 133-131 on Monday...
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers rally past Celtics 133-131 after Tyrese Haliburton injures hamstring

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 32 points, Chet Holmgren added 31 and the Oklahoma City Thunder led most of the way in a 136-128 victory over the Washington Wizards on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander, Holmgren lead Thunder past Wizards 136-128

headlines.description: — Kyle Lowry got hurt and left the game while he was still in the game. He didn't even wait for play to stop, simply exiting the floor and temporarily having Miami play 5-on-4 for a few seconds.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat get 28 from Herro, 22 from Adebayo and top Rockets 120-113

headlines.description: — Jordan Clarkson and Lauri Markkanen had 21 points apiece and the Utah Jazz staved off a second-half rally for a 132-116 victory over Milwaukee, the Bucks fourth loss in five games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clarkson, Markkanen each score 21 to lead Jazz past Bucks 132-116

headlines.description: — Paul George scored 25 points, Ivica Zubac added 19 and the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Phoenix Suns 138-111 for the...
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers rout Suns 138-111 for 2nd time in 5 days behind George and Zubac
